overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. I conducted
  a thorough review of the existing design, identifying areas for improvement in
  color, typography, layout, and component styling. The core approach involved
  transitioning to a calming, sleep-themed color palette with deep indigos,
  purples, and teal accents. I then systematically updated various UI elements,
  including the main form layout, progress bar, intro section (introducing
  feature cards and refined alerts), and individual form components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. The report section also received a
  significant visual overhaul to align with the new theme. The goal was to
  create a more professional, inviting, and emotionally resonant interface,
  moving away from a basic template look to a design with distinct personality
  and trustworthiness. After implementing the changes, I verified the visual
  consistency and impact through a browser review.
